<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc2ab154a-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s1153"><num value="1153">§ 1153.</num><heading> Aggravation</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A preexisting injury or disease will be considered to have been aggravated by active military, naval, air, or space service, where there is an increase in disability during such service, unless there is a specific finding that the increase in disability is due to the natural progress of the disease.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc2ab154b-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(<ref href="/us/pl/85/857">Pub. L. 85–857</ref>, <date date="1958-09-02">Sept. 2, 1958</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/72/1124">72 Stat. 1124</ref>, § 353; renumbered § 1153, <ref href="/us/pl/102/83/s5/a">Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(a)</ref>, <date date="1991-08-06">Aug. 6, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/406">105 Stat. 406</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/116/283/dA/tIX/s926/a/15">Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title IX, § 926(a)(15)</ref>, <date date="2021-01-01">Jan. 1, 2021</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/134/3830">134 Stat. 3830</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
